SIMPLE: speechless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Speechless
<hw>Speech"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute or
deprived of the faculty of speech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not speaking for a time; dumb; mute;
silent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Speechless</qex> with wonder, and half dead with fear.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Speech"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Speech"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Speechmaker</ent>⟦br⟧
